<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="652" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,760,761,2064]" pageId="1" pageNumber="652">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,402,761,784]" pageId="1" pageNumber="652">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
Antennae (
<figureCitation box="[529,609,761,784]" captionStart="Figs 17‒26" captionStartId="5.[150,187,997,1016]" captionTargetBox="[156,1428,190,954]" captionTargetId="figure-438@5.[150,1436,190,957]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 17‒26. Lasionota (Arqueozodes) spp. 17‒19 ‒ head, frontal view: 17 ‒ L. (A.) cidburmeisteri sp. nov., 18 ‒ L. (A.) aonikenk sp. nov., 19 ‒ L. (A.) sulcata (Moore, 1997). 20‒21 ‒ L. (A.) cidburmeisteri sp. nov., aedeagus: 20 ‒ dorsal view; 21 ‒ ventral view.22‒23 ‒L.(A.) aonikenk sp. nov., aedeagus: 22 ‒ dorsal view; 23 ‒ ventral view. 24 ‒ L. (A.) aonikenk sp. nov., last tergites and ovipositor of female. 25‒26 ‒ L. (A.) sulcata, aedeagus: 25 ‒ dorsal view; 26 ‒ ventral view. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177960" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177960/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="652">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
) serrate from antennomere IV; antennomeres V‒X as long as wide (
<taxonomicName authority="Cid-Arcos &amp; Campodonico, 2020" authorityName="Cid-Arcos &amp; Campodonico" authorityYear="2020" box="[160,340,824,848]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Lasionota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="652" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aonikenk" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Arqueozodes">
<emphasis box="[160,182,825,848]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="652">L.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[201,224,824,847]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="652">A.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[243,340,824,848]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="652">aonikenk</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[350,436,825,848]" pageId="1" pageNumber="652" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
with antennomeres V‒X wi- der than long). Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[448,549,857,880]" captionStart="Figs 1‒6" captionStartId="2.[151,188,1998,2017]" captionTargetBox="[195,1393,193,1921]" captionTargetId="figure-13@2.[180,1408,165,1941]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1‒6. Lasionota (Arqueozodes) cidburmeisteri sp. nov. 1‒3 ‒ male: 1 ‒ dorsal view; 2 ‒ ventral view; 3 ‒ lateral view; 4‒6 ‒ female: 4 ‒ dorsal view; 5 ‒ ventral view; 6 ‒ lateral view. Scale bars = 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177952" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177952/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="652">Figs 1, 4</figureCitation>
) with pair of deep depressions before lateral margins; basal angles acutely produced (
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Moore" baseAuthorityYear="1997" box="[267,439,920,944]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Lasionota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="652" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sulcata" subGenus="Arqueozodes">
<emphasis box="[267,289,921,944]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="652">L.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[322,345,920,943]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="652">A.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[362,439,920,944]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="652">sulcata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Cid-Arcos &amp; Campodonico, 2020" authorityName="Cid-Arcos &amp; Campodonico" authorityYear="2020" box="[494,668,920,944]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Lasionota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="652" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aonikenk" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Arqueozodes">
<emphasis box="[494,515,921,944]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="652">L.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[532,555,920,943]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="652">A.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[572,668,920,944]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="652">aonikenk</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[676,760,921,944]" pageId="1" pageNumber="652" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
with depressions before lateral margins shallow, basal angles blunt). Prosternum (
<figureCitation box="[443,539,985,1008]" captionStart="Figs 1‒6" captionStartId="2.[151,188,1998,2017]" captionTargetBox="[195,1393,193,1921]" captionTargetId="figure-13@2.[180,1408,165,1941]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1‒6. Lasionota (Arqueozodes) cidburmeisteri sp. nov. 1‒3 ‒ male: 1 ‒ dorsal view; 2 ‒ ventral view; 3 ‒ lateral view; 4‒6 ‒ female: 4 ‒ dorsal view; 5 ‒ ventral view; 6 ‒ lateral view. Scale bars = 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177952" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177952/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="652">Figs 2, 5</figureCitation>
) red (
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Moore" baseAuthorityYear="1997" box="[605,760,984,1008]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Lasionota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="652" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sulcata" subGenus="Arqueozodes">
<emphasis box="[605,627,985,1008]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="652">L.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[643,667,984,1007]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="652">A.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[683,760,984,1008]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="652">sulcata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Cid-Arcos &amp; Campodonico, 2020" authorityName="Cid-Arcos &amp; Campodonico" authorityYear="2020" box="[200,378,1016,1040]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Lasionota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="652" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aonikenk" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Arqueozodes">
<emphasis box="[200,222,1017,1040]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="652">L.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[240,264,1016,1039]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="652">A.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[282,378,1016,1040]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="652">aonikenk</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[389,475,1017,1040]" pageId="1" pageNumber="652" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
with prosternum metallic coloured). Scutellum (
<figureCitation box="[397,499,1049,1072]" captionStart="Figs 1‒6" captionStartId="2.[151,188,1998,2017]" captionTargetBox="[195,1393,193,1921]" captionTargetId="figure-13@2.[180,1408,165,1941]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1‒6. Lasionota (Arqueozodes) cidburmeisteri sp. nov. 1‒3 ‒ male: 1 ‒ dorsal view; 2 ‒ ventral view; 3 ‒ lateral view; 4‒6 ‒ female: 4 ‒ dorsal view; 5 ‒ ventral view; 6 ‒ lateral view. Scale bars = 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177952" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177952/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="652">Figs 1, 4</figureCitation>
) as an inverted regular pentagon (
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Moore" baseAuthorityYear="1997" box="[262,409,1080,1104]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Lasionota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="652" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sulcata" subGenus="Arqueozodes">
<emphasis box="[262,283,1081,1104]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="652">L.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[296,320,1080,1103]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="652">A.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[333,409,1080,1104]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="652">sulcata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Cid-Arcos &amp; Campodonico, 2020" authorityName="Cid-Arcos &amp; Campodonico" authorityYear="2020" box="[457,623,1080,1104]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Lasionota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="652" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aonikenk" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Arqueozodes">
<emphasis box="[457,479,1081,1104]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="652">L.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[492,515,1080,1103]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="652">A.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[528,623,1080,1104]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="652">aonikenk</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[628,709,1081,1104]" pageId="1" pageNumber="652" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
with scutellum cordiform). Elytra (
<figureCitation box="[465,557,1113,1136]" captionStart="Figs 1‒6" captionStartId="2.[151,188,1998,2017]" captionTargetBox="[195,1393,193,1921]" captionTargetId="figure-13@2.[180,1408,165,1941]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1‒6. Lasionota (Arqueozodes) cidburmeisteri sp. nov. 1‒3 ‒ male: 1 ‒ dorsal view; 2 ‒ ventral view; 3 ‒ lateral view; 4‒6 ‒ female: 4 ‒ dorsal view; 5 ‒ ventral view; 6 ‒ lateral view. Scale bars = 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177952" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177952/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="652">Figs 1, 4</figureCitation>
) with apex without periapical teeth (
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Moore" baseAuthorityYear="1997" box="[334,490,1144,1168]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Lasionota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="652" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sulcata" subGenus="Arqueozodes">
<emphasis box="[334,356,1145,1168]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="652">L.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[373,396,1144,1167]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="652">A.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[413,490,1144,1168]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="652">sulcata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Cid-Arcos &amp; Campodonico, 2020" authorityName="Cid-Arcos &amp; Campodonico" authorityYear="2020" box="[545,721,1144,1168]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Lasionota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="652" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aonikenk" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Arqueozodes">
<emphasis box="[545,567,1145,1168]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="652">L.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[584,608,1144,1167]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="652">A.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[625,721,1144,1168]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="652">aonikenk</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="1" pageNumber="652" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
with apex of elytra with periapical teeth). Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[158,277,1209,1232]" captionStart="Figs 17‒26" captionStartId="5.[150,187,997,1016]" captionTargetBox="[156,1428,190,954]" captionTargetId="figure-438@5.[150,1436,190,957]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 17‒26. Lasionota (Arqueozodes) spp. 17‒19 ‒ head, frontal view: 17 ‒ L. (A.) cidburmeisteri sp. nov., 18 ‒ L. (A.) aonikenk sp. nov., 19 ‒ L. (A.) sulcata (Moore, 1997). 20‒21 ‒ L. (A.) cidburmeisteri sp. nov., aedeagus: 20 ‒ dorsal view; 21 ‒ ventral view.22‒23 ‒L.(A.) aonikenk sp. nov., aedeagus: 22 ‒ dorsal view; 23 ‒ ventral view. 24 ‒ L. (A.) aonikenk sp. nov., last tergites and ovipositor of female. 25‒26 ‒ L. (A.) sulcata, aedeagus: 25 ‒ dorsal view; 26 ‒ ventral view. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177960" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177960/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="652">Figs 20‒21</figureCitation>
) with median lobe cuneiform (
<taxonomicName authority="Cid-Arcos &amp; Campodonico, 2020" authorityName="Cid-Arcos &amp; Campodonico" authorityYear="2020" box="[594,760,1208,1232]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Lasionota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="652" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aonikenk" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Arqueozodes">
<emphasis box="[594,616,1209,1232]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="652">L.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[629,652,1208,1231]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="652">A.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[665,760,1208,1232]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="652">aonikenk</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[151,234,1241,1264]" pageId="1" pageNumber="652" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
with median lobe wide).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="652" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,760,761,2064]" pageId="1" pageNumber="652">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,291,1273,1296]" pageId="1" pageNumber="652">Description.</emphasis>
<typeStatus box="[301,401,1273,1296]" pageId="1" pageNumber="652">Holotype</typeStatus>
male, 13.6 mm length; 4.8 mm width.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,760,761,2064]" pageId="1" pageNumber="652">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[181,240,1337,1360]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="652">Head</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[253,328,1337,1360]" captionStart="Figs 17‒26" captionStartId="5.[150,187,997,1016]" captionTargetBox="[156,1428,190,954]" captionTargetId="figure-438@5.[150,1436,190,957]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 17‒26. Lasionota (Arqueozodes) spp. 17‒19 ‒ head, frontal view: 17 ‒ L. (A.) cidburmeisteri sp. nov., 18 ‒ L. (A.) aonikenk sp. nov., 19 ‒ L. (A.) sulcata (Moore, 1997). 20‒21 ‒ L. (A.) cidburmeisteri sp. nov., aedeagus: 20 ‒ dorsal view; 21 ‒ ventral view.22‒23 ‒L.(A.) aonikenk sp. nov., aedeagus: 22 ‒ dorsal view; 23 ‒ ventral view. 24 ‒ L. (A.) aonikenk sp. nov., last tergites and ovipositor of female. 25‒26 ‒ L. (A.) sulcata, aedeagus: 25 ‒ dorsal view; 26 ‒ ventral view. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177960" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177960/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="652">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
) with shallow and inconspicuous depression in interocular zone; punctuation dense and regular; pilosity long, fine, decumbent and pale white. Eyes not produced, with interior margins subparallel. Antennae (
<figureCitation box="[159,235,1465,1488]" captionStart="Figs 17‒26" captionStartId="5.[150,187,997,1016]" captionTargetBox="[156,1428,190,954]" captionTargetId="figure-438@5.[150,1436,190,957]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 17‒26. Lasionota (Arqueozodes) spp. 17‒19 ‒ head, frontal view: 17 ‒ L. (A.) cidburmeisteri sp. nov., 18 ‒ L. (A.) aonikenk sp. nov., 19 ‒ L. (A.) sulcata (Moore, 1997). 20‒21 ‒ L. (A.) cidburmeisteri sp. nov., aedeagus: 20 ‒ dorsal view; 21 ‒ ventral view.22‒23 ‒L.(A.) aonikenk sp. nov., aedeagus: 22 ‒ dorsal view; 23 ‒ ventral view. 24 ‒ L. (A.) aonikenk sp. nov., last tergites and ovipositor of female. 25‒26 ‒ L. (A.) sulcata, aedeagus: 25 ‒ dorsal view; 26 ‒ ventral view. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177960" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177960/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="652">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
) reach anterior quarter of pronotum; serrated and with sensory pits starting from antennomere IV; with moderately long sub-erect setae; antennomeres V‒X nearly as long as wide.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,760,761,2064]" pageId="1" pageNumber="652">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[181,271,1593,1616]" pageId="1" pageNumber="652">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[181,264,1593,1616]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="652">Thorax</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[406,510,1593,1616]" captionStart="Figs 1‒6" captionStartId="2.[151,188,1998,2017]" captionTargetBox="[195,1393,193,1921]" captionTargetId="figure-13@2.[180,1408,165,1941]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1‒6. Lasionota (Arqueozodes) cidburmeisteri sp. nov. 1‒3 ‒ male: 1 ‒ dorsal view; 2 ‒ ventral view; 3 ‒ lateral view; 4‒6 ‒ female: 4 ‒ dorsal view; 5 ‒ ventral view; 6 ‒ lateral view. Scale bars = 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177952" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177952/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="652">Figs 1, 4</figureCitation>
) distinctly wider than long; punctuation dense and irregular, coarser than on head, being stronger in anterior half; pilosity pale white, long, dense, fine and decumbent; basal half of disc with moderate to distinct depression medially and with pair of deep depressions on sides before lateral margins; lateral margin with red colour not reaching basal margin; basal margin bisinuate, with produced basal angles. Hypomerae (
<figureCitation box="[159,309,1849,1872]" captionStart="Figs 1‒6" captionStartId="2.[151,188,1998,2017]" captionTargetBox="[195,1393,193,1921]" captionTargetId="figure-13@2.[180,1408,165,1941]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1‒6. Lasionota (Arqueozodes) cidburmeisteri sp. nov. 1‒3 ‒ male: 1 ‒ dorsal view; 2 ‒ ventral view; 3 ‒ lateral view; 4‒6 ‒ female: 4 ‒ dorsal view; 5 ‒ ventral view; 6 ‒ lateral view. Scale bars = 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177952" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177952/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="652">Figs 2‒3, 5‒6</figureCitation>
) bright red, excluding metallic blue basal margin; punctation dense and regular; pilosity moderately long, fine and decumbent. Prosternum (
<figureCitation box="[581,679,1913,1936]" captionStart="Figs 1‒6" captionStartId="2.[151,188,1998,2017]" captionTargetBox="[195,1393,193,1921]" captionTargetId="figure-13@2.[180,1408,165,1941]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1‒6. Lasionota (Arqueozodes) cidburmeisteri sp. nov. 1‒3 ‒ male: 1 ‒ dorsal view; 2 ‒ ventral view; 3 ‒ lateral view; 4‒6 ‒ female: 4 ‒ dorsal view; 5 ‒ ventral view; 6 ‒ lateral view. Scale bars = 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177952" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177952/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="652">Figs 2, 5</figureCitation>
) bright red, with dense and fine setigerous punctation; pilosity moderately long, dense, fine and decumbent; basal margin with metallic blue fringe. Scutellum (
<figureCitation box="[559,658,2009,2032]" captionStart="Figs 1‒6" captionStartId="2.[151,188,1998,2017]" captionTargetBox="[195,1393,193,1921]" captionTargetId="figure-13@2.[180,1408,165,1941]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1‒6. Lasionota (Arqueozodes) cidburmeisteri sp. nov. 1‒3 ‒ male: 1 ‒ dorsal view; 2 ‒ ventral view; 3 ‒ lateral view; 4‒6 ‒ female: 4 ‒ dorsal view; 5 ‒ ventral view; 6 ‒ lateral view. Scale bars = 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177952" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177952/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="652">Figs 1, 4</figureCitation>
) smooth, metallic blue and regularly pentagonal.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[828,1443,190,1173]" pageId="1" pageNumber="652">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[858,926,190,213]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="652">Elytra</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[941,1038,190,213]" captionStart="Figs 1‒6" captionStartId="2.[151,188,1998,2017]" captionTargetBox="[195,1393,193,1921]" captionTargetId="figure-13@2.[180,1408,165,1941]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1‒6. Lasionota (Arqueozodes) cidburmeisteri sp. nov. 1‒3 ‒ male: 1 ‒ dorsal view; 2 ‒ ventral view; 3 ‒ lateral view; 4‒6 ‒ female: 4 ‒ dorsal view; 5 ‒ ventral view; 6 ‒ lateral view. Scale bars = 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177952" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177952/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="652">Figs 1, 4</figureCitation>
) with sparse inconspicuous and long setae. Background colour bluish black. Four wide orange yellow bands reaching lateral margin of elytra; basal band reaching elytral suture after projecting slightly towards apex; second (sub-basal) band not reaching elytral suture, narrowed at middle, widened at lateral margin of elytra and connected to first band; third (sub-distal) band not reaching elytral suture, slightly curved; distal band semicircular, not reaching elytral suture nor apex. Elytral suture slightly elevated. Costae complete, almost straight, with coarse series of double punctures between each other; first costa two times wider than others in basal half and with inconspicuous fine punctation. Humeral callus as wide as first costa. Apex without periapical teeth.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[828,1443,190,1173]" pageId="1" pageNumber="652">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[858,962,638,661]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="652">Abdomen</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[974,1065,638,661]" captionStart="Figs 1‒6" captionStartId="2.[151,188,1998,2017]" captionTargetBox="[195,1393,193,1921]" captionTargetId="figure-13@2.[180,1408,165,1941]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1‒6. Lasionota (Arqueozodes) cidburmeisteri sp. nov. 1‒3 ‒ male: 1 ‒ dorsal view; 2 ‒ ventral view; 3 ‒ lateral view; 4‒6 ‒ female: 4 ‒ dorsal view; 5 ‒ ventral view; 6 ‒ lateral view. Scale bars = 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177952" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177952/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="652">Figs 2, 5</figureCitation>
) metallic blue; densely and regularly punctate; and covered with long, decumbent pale white setae; first ventrite with oval red spot along middle, not reaching distal margin.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[828,1443,190,1173]" pageId="1" pageNumber="652">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[858,964,766,789]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="652">Aedeagus</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[976,1094,766,789]" captionStart="Figs 17‒26" captionStartId="5.[150,187,997,1016]" captionTargetBox="[156,1428,190,954]" captionTargetId="figure-438@5.[150,1436,190,957]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 17‒26. Lasionota (Arqueozodes) spp. 17‒19 ‒ head, frontal view: 17 ‒ L. (A.) cidburmeisteri sp. nov., 18 ‒ L. (A.) aonikenk sp. nov., 19 ‒ L. (A.) sulcata (Moore, 1997). 20‒21 ‒ L. (A.) cidburmeisteri sp. nov., aedeagus: 20 ‒ dorsal view; 21 ‒ ventral view.22‒23 ‒L.(A.) aonikenk sp. nov., aedeagus: 22 ‒ dorsal view; 23 ‒ ventral view. 24 ‒ L. (A.) aonikenk sp. nov., last tergites and ovipositor of female. 25‒26 ‒ L. (A.) sulcata, aedeagus: 25 ‒ dorsal view; 26 ‒ ventral view. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177960" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177960/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="652">Figs 20‒21</figureCitation>
) tubular, with sides of parameres subparallel, strong longitudinal depression in two distal thirds; median lobe cuneiform, margins converging in apical portion; basal lobe narrowed by sides.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[828,1443,190,1173]" pageId="1" pageNumber="652">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[858,1073,894,917]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="652">Sexual dimorphism.</emphasis>
Apical margin of last ventrite (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figs 1‒6" captionStartId="2.[151,188,1998,2017]" captionTargetBox="[195,1393,193,1921]" captionTargetId="figure-13@2.[180,1408,165,1941]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1‒6. Lasionota (Arqueozodes) cidburmeisteri sp. nov. 1‒3 ‒ male: 1 ‒ dorsal view; 2 ‒ ventral view; 3 ‒ lateral view; 4‒6 ‒ female: 4 ‒ dorsal view; 5 ‒ ventral view; 6 ‒ lateral view. Scale bars = 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177952" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177952/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="652">Figs 2, 5</figureCitation>
) notched in males and semicircular in females.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[828,1443,190,1173]" pageId="1" pageNumber="652">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[858,1110,958,981]" pageId="1" pageNumber="652">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[858,1103,958,981]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="652">Intraspecific variation</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Apex of elytra with tooth pointed or blunt.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[828,1443,190,1173]" pageId="1" pageNumber="652">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[858,1166,1022,1045]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="652">
Measurements of 
<typeStatus box="[1054,1162,1022,1045]" pageId="1" pageNumber="652">paratypes</typeStatus>
.
</emphasis>
Males (n = 4): 13.3‒14.5 mm length; 5.0‒5.5 mm width. Females (n = 4) 14.0‒15.3 mm length; 5.0‒5.7 mm width.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="652" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="1.[828,1443,190,1173]" pageId="1" pageNumber="652">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[828,956,1118,1141]" pageId="1" pageNumber="652">Etymology.</emphasis>
Named after 
<collectingCountry box="[1106,1204,1118,1141]" name="Mauritius" pageId="1" pageNumber="652">Mauricio</collectingCountry>
Cid Burmeister, who collected most specimens of this new species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
